   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">By connecting an optional portable audio device to the AUX input jack (stereo mini jack) on the unit and then simply selecting the source, you can listen on your car speakers.</p>
         <fig class="- topic/fig ">
            <image href="media/image506a.png"
                   placement="inline"
                   class="- topic/image "/>
         </fig>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Turn the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">VOLUME</b> dial left to decrease the volume level.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">AUX</b> volume can also be controlled separately through the connected device.</p>
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="media/image561a.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Turn the external audio equipment off Open the cover, connect
the audio output of the external audio equipment to AUX input
terminal on the unit.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Turn the external audio equipment on. Start playback of the external audio
        equipment at a moderate volume. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_i2d_pss_5gc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image554.png"
                            id="image_l2d_pss_5gc"
                            placement="inline"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">AUX</b> button to select the AUX function.
        </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="media/image617a.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Set your usual listening volume by turn the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">VOLUME</b> dial left/right on the
          unit.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Once the connector is disconnected, the previous mode will be restored.</p>
               <p class="- topic/p ">AUX
          mode can be used only when an external audio player has been connected.</p>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
